method.doc:
Gets the current fort::myrmidon::Time::Time and fort::myrmidon::Time::Time. This time will both have a wall and a
monotonic clock reading associated with the
fort::myrmidon::Time::SYSTEM_MONOTONIC_CLOCK. Therefore such idioms:

```
Time start = Time::Now();
SomeFunction();
Duration ellapsed = Time::Now().Sub(start);
```

Will always return a positive Duration, even if the wall clock
has been reset between the two calls to Now
